Quote: At the Warden's Court yesterday Mr Warden Bush stated that, for the future, plans of water races, machine, special or business sites, or for any other right or privilege for which a plan is required, must be deposited in the Warden's Office within three months of the lodging of the application, that being the time limited by the statute for the survey and depositing of plans for special claims and licensed holdinge [sic], unless an extension of time has been applied for and granted.
